"{\"uid\": \"rollingstone.com-culture-culture-features-olympics-afghan-women-interview-1235072029\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByAbigail Pesta For women and girls inAfghanistan, life has become one big \\\"No.\\\"\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 81, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ByAbigail Pesta\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 15}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 20, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"girls inAfghanistan\", \"from\": 30, \"to\": 49}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 55}, {\"ngram\": \"one big \\\"No\", \"from\": 67, \"to\": 78}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No school beyond the sixth grade.\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No school\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 92}, {\"ngram\": \"the sixth grade\", \"from\": 100, \"to\": 115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No traveling without a male guardian.\", \"from\": 117, \"to\": 154, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a male guardian\", \"from\": 138, \"to\": 153}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Death by stoning for \\\"moral crimes\\\" such as adultery.\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 208, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Death\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 160}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"moral crimes\", \"from\": 176, \"to\": 189}, {\"ngram\": \"adultery\", \"from\": 199, \"to\": 207}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In most places, women must cover themselves from head to toe if they leave the house.\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 294, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"most places\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 223}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 230}, {\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 262}, {\"ngram\": \"toe\", \"from\": 266, \"to\": 269}, {\"ngram\": \"the house\", \"from\": 284, \"to\": 293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And playingsportsis forbidden, too.\", \"from\": 295, \"to\": 330, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When theTalibanregained control of the country in 2021, the regime immediately clamped down on women's rights, erasing decades of hard-won gains.\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 477, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"control\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 363}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 367, \"to\": 378}, {\"ngram\": \"the regime\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 398}, {\"ngram\": \"women's rights\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 441}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 458}, {\"ngram\": \"hard-won gains\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 476}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the first moves was to ban access to sports for women and girls, saying such activities would \\\"expose\\\" their bodies.\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first moves\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 528}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 538}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"such activities\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 572}, {\"ngram\": \"their bodies\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 600}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Women athletes became targets for retribution,\\\" says Mara Gubuan, founder of the nonprofit Equality League, which helped evacuate and resettle dozens of female athletes.\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 772, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women athletes\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 617}, {\"ngram\": \"targets\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 632}, {\"ngram\": \"retribution\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 648}, {\"ngram\": \"Mara Gubuan\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 667}, {\"ngram\": \"founder\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 676}, {\"ngram\": \"the nonprofit Equality League\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 709}, {\"ngram\": \"evacuate and resettle dozens\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 752}, {\"ngram\": \"female athletes\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But some Afghan women are finding ways \\\"to challenge the Taliban's tyranny,\\\" says Minky Worden, director of global initiatives for Human Rights Watch.\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 783, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999326974, \"rank\": 6.774007753929325e-11, \"text\": \"Afghan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 831, \"end\": 838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"score\": 0.9999991025583247, \"rank\": 8.974422970819794e-07, \"text\": \"Taliban\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\"}, {\"begin\": 856, \"end\": 868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minky_Worden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Minky Worden\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minky_Worden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minky_Worden\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 812}, {\"ngram\": \"director\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"global initiatives\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 900}, {\"ngram\": \"Human Rights Watch\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Women athletes have shown enormous resilience by evacuating themselves and rebuilding their national teams in soccer, cricket, and other sports.\\\"\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 1071, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women athletes\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"enormous resilience\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 971}, {\"ngram\": \"their national teams\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1032}, {\"ngram\": \"soccer\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1042}, {\"ngram\": \"cricket\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1051}, {\"ngram\": \"other sports\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the athletes taking a stand are three women now representing Afghanistan in the Paris Games - cyclist sistersFaribaandYulduz Hashimi, who now live in exile in Italy, and sprinterKamia Yousufi, who lives in exile in Australia.\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1140, \"end\": 1151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9361858381378713, \"rank\": 0.06816398973665337, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 1238, \"end\": 1243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9960092166302092, \"rank\": 0.00400676289553004, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 1294, \"end\": 1303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999998708954164, \"rank\": 1.290988741962974e-07, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1091}, {\"ngram\": \"a stand\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1106}, {\"ngram\": \"three women\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games - cyclist sistersFaribaandYulduz Hashimi\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1211}, {\"ngram\": \"exile\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"Yousufi\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1270}, {\"ngram\": \"exile\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1290}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three men, two of whom live in exile as well, round out the team.\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1370, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Three men\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1314}, {\"ngram\": \"exile\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1341}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They carry the former Afghanistan flag; Taliban officials are not allowed at the Games.\", \"from\": 1371, \"to\": 1458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1393, \"end\": 1404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9361858381378713, \"rank\": 0.06816398973665337, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"score\": 0.9999991025583247, \"rank\": 8.974422970819794e-07, \"text\": \"Taliban\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1457}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But not everyone supports the idea of an Afghan Olympic team.\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1501, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999326974, \"rank\": 6.774007753929325e-11, \"text\": \"Afghan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"not everyone\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1476}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Friba Rezayee, one of Afghanistan's first two female Olympians in 2004, argued in a recentNew York Timeseditorialthat the International Olympic Committee should bar the team representing Afghanistan, to demonstrate that it values human rights.\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1522, \"end\": 1535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fariba_Rezayee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Friba Rezayee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fariba_Rezayee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fariba_Rezayee\"}, {\"begin\": 1544, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9361858381378713, \"rank\": 